metadata.name: tr4ns4ctions #33
metadata.description:
Tr4ns4ctions is a series of real-time animations that use pixels to create an abstraction of the movement of values. The pixels are constantly rearranging, being transferred from offer to taker, liquify, appear and disappear. They are forming endless compositions, sometimes intransparent or with strange spins.

The level of abstraction has been set to a 2x pixel size and the color palette of the NES with 12 different color modes. 16 pixel patterns serve as the fundamental building blocks and a simplex noise field determines the direction of movement.

click || space => pause/unpause

View all tr4ns4ctions at https://tr4ns4ctions.com

Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: Labyrinth #39
metadata.description:
I have just emerged from a Labyrinth
of intricate mazes
where I was caught.
Limp from my wounds, defeated,
I turn to my fate
to my old companions,
my doubts, my misgivings.

("The Labyrinth" by Jorge Luis Borges, translated by Alastair Reid)

"Labyrinth" is a journey through abstract shapes, where chaos and order entwine as an enigmatic puzzle. The color palettes are the guiding stars in ‚Äòlabyrinth‚Äô. Each palette offers a distinct path through the composition, from monochromes to bold and contrasting hues, they dictate the intricate design of ‚Äòlabyrinth‚Äô.

To save a PNG file, press [s].

30& of earnings form Royalties go to Processing Foundation

Script, 2023

metadata.name: Ethereal Microcosm #68
metadata.description:
An exploration of algorithmic organisms in a contained environment.

This piece is about the simulation of microscopic patterns using a high number of even tinier agents all following the same rules. Different species evolve and interact together, resulting in stabilizing patterns out of their parametric configurations. A form of artificial life.

This work is based on the paper "Characteristics of pattern formation and evolution in approximations of physarum transport networks", written by Jeff Jones and popularized in the artistic field by Sage Jenson. Some features were added to increase the visual and behavioral complexity of the system. Agents are divided into different species, with their own set of rules and interacting with their own substrate. Substrates also interact with each other and agents will mutate in contact of some of them.

NFT License
Runs properly on Chrome 97.0.4692.99
GPU intensive

Press P to pause (double tab touch devices)

metadata.name: Atmosphere #102
metadata.description:
Atmosphere is a 3D interactive and generative piece creating an organic cube or sphere. ‚Ä®You can turn around and zoom in or let it live.
The size, position and frequency of shapes are generated for each token, along with the color theme. ‚Ä®Movements and positions are generated by a noise and a seed, it‚Äôs the same for each view.

‚Ä®On live version the visual fit your screen.

Shortcuts on live version :
	- press ‚Äòp‚Äô to stop the motion and explore
	- press ‚Äòf‚Äô to launch the fullscreen mode
	- press ‚Äòh‚Äô to hide the cursor and `cmd/ctrl + s` to save a PNG.

Features :
	- Duo tone - Theme has 2 colors
	- Direction - Direction of the movements of shapes (x, y, none or all)
	- Rotation - Rotation of shapes (x,z, all or none)
	- Main Shape - sphere or box
	- Shapes - cylinder, cube, plane or torus 
	- Scalable - If the  motion impact the scale of shapes or not

Created by Quentin Hocd√©, in Brussels (Belgium).

metadata.name: Celebrate the D2 #59
metadata.description:
Fixed a bug in the original project.
It can now actually output uniform patterns :-)
 
A fun free mint to celebrate 500 followers on Twitter.
The project is open for 24 hours, for all to mint.
And after that, the remaining editions get burned.

The base shape is a "super ellipse", made famous by (among others) danish inventor and polymath Piet Hein.
